  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As I said before, Schindler got the permission to move his factory and got the permission to make it much bigger than it was in Krakow.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That means he also needed much more workers than he had.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he got the permission or he allowed himself to take 800 men and 300 women.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then began the-- this today so very famous Schindler's list.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The list was made [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] through, first of all, through Schindler.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And his only condition was to put on the list his workers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It means people who were coming from his factory, the 350, and a few others that he left with the time and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that he wanted them.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The others were put on the list by-- everybody who saw the film or who read the book written by Keneally knows that there was a famous man who-- it was Itzhak Stern.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The film shows that Itzhak Stern was making the list with the-- which ended together, which is not too accurate.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "By the way, if I may, I would say that there are some details in the film or in the book which are not accurate.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There's no one lie.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There's nothing that-- that wasn't true.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it doesn't mean too much if they mixed or, or, or related it otherwise.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But if I am telling of the story so I want to make it more accurate because [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] the, the man-- one of the man who, who made the Schindler was really-- make the list was really Stern.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But the main man who made the list was the man who-- who was in charge of, of so-called, I should call it manpower organization today.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
